    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1738"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1738">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/213.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Decision of Justice of Supreme Court regarding Costa Rica boundary continues to
                    monopolize political discussion of newspapers and National Assembly. Panaman
                    President submitted same National Assembly stating that the decision subtracted
                    from the Loubet award,<note n="6" xml:id="d1738fn6">
                        <ref target="frus1910#pg_786">For. Rel. 1910, pp 786</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1910#pg_787">787</ref>.</note> did not take into
                    consideration [cause?], and gives Panama less territory than the Costa Rican
                    representative before Loubet admitted belonged to Panama.</p>
                <p>Members of Assembly presented protest refusing to abide by decision unless
                    compelled by superior force. Same action by the Senate upon statement of
                    administration leader that it reflected sentiment of administration but that
                    results could be accomplished better in some manner such as Costa Rica adopted
                    in the matter of Loubet award. Committee of lawyers appointed by citizens
                    meeting and committee of National Assembly to study decision, resolution of
                    latter calling for Panaman Minister at Washington to express opinion both on
                    decision and best method of avoiding compliance with it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
